{
  "schema_version": "lmctl/v3",
  "definition_schema_version": 3,
  "name": "bugfix-pr-fixer-v2",
  "version": 1,
  "description": "Claims a bugfix project work item, fixes it with a coder/reviewer loop, and prepares the project for pull-request follow-up.",
  "estimated_duration_ms": 300000,
  "default_task_timeout_ms": 1800000,
  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "s-feasibility-b195",
      "name": "feasibility",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Evaluate the feasibility of fixing this GitHub issue: {{job_payload.issue_url}}\n\nRun `gh issue view {{job_payload.issue_url}} --json title,body,labels` to read the issue. Decide one outcome:\n- `tractable`: clear repro path; bug is fixable with a focused code change + test\n- `blocked_setup`: needs environment/tooling not available here\n- `requires_clarification`: issue body is too vague to start\n- `failed`: gh call errored\n\nClose with STANCE: <tractable|blocked_setup|requires_clarification|failed>"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-reproduce-7226",
      "name": "reproduce",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 2
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Work in {{project.local_path}}. If that directory does not contain a checkout of {{project.owner}}/{{project.repo}}, `git clone https://github.com/{{project.owner}}/{{project.repo}}.git {{project.local_path}}` first. Then `cd {{project.local_path}}` before any further commands. Do NOT operate inside your agent sessiondir.\n\nReproduce the bug reported in {{job_payload.issue_url}}:\n1. `gh issue view {{job_payload.issue_url}}` to read the body.\n2. Install dependencies if needed (the project's test command is the focused_test step downstream — match it).\n3. Write the minimum repro from the issue body inside {{project.local_path}}.\n4. Run the project's test command against the bug's area to confirm reproduction (the repro should fail before the fix).\n5. Save the repro snippet so the reviewer can verify.\n\nReturn STANCE: <reproduced|failed>"
        },
        "reviewers": [
          {
            "team": "default",
            "alias": "Reviewer1"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-root-cause-0017",
      "name": "root_cause",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first; investigate inside the project checkout, not your sessiondir.\n\nYou just reproduced {{job_payload.issue_url}}. Find the root cause:\n1. Investigate the codebase via grep/cat/etc inside {{project.local_path}}.\n2. Identify the exact file + line + reason for the bug.\n3. Return STANCE: <found|hypothesized|none|failed>"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-fix-733b",
      "name": "fix",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first. All git operations must happen in the project checkout, NOT your sessiondir — the branch + commit are read back from {{project.local_path}} by downstream steps.\n\nApply the fix you root-caused for {{job_payload.issue_url}}:\n1. `cd {{project.local_path}}` and create a feature branch: `git checkout -b lmctl-next/run-{{run_id}}-issue-X` (replace X with the issue number).\n2. Edit the buggy file.\n3. Add a regression test in the project's test layout (tests/, *_test.go, etc.).\n4. Run the project's test command (matches the focused_test step downstream) to confirm all tests pass.\n5. `git add` + `git commit` on the branch with a concise subject like `Fix issue #X: <short summary>`.\n\nSTANCE: <applied|failed>"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-focused-test-bc8f",
      "name": "focused_test",
      "type": "lmctl/shell-step",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "command": "{{project.test_command}}",
        "outcomes_from_exit": {
          "0": "@terminal:exit_0",
          "default": "@terminal:exit_default"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-code-review-ecad",
      "name": "code_review",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 3
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "`cd {{project.local_path}}` first. Confirm the fix for {{job_payload.issue_url}} is committed on the feature branch and tests pass.\n\nRun `git log -1` to verify the commit exists and `git diff <repo-default-branch>..HEAD --stat` (the repo's actual default branch: usually `main` or `master`) to summarize. Verify HEAD is on the feature branch you created in the fix step.\n\nSTANCE: committed | failed"
        },
        "reviewers": [
          {
            "team": "default",
            "alias": "Reviewer1"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-internal-pr-artifact-b035",
      "name": "internal_pr_artifact",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Draft a PR body for the fix you applied to {{job_payload.issue_url}}.\n\nInclude: brief problem statement, root cause, the change, focused test summary. NO emoji, NO AI tells (claude/codex/gemini/anthropic/openai), NO 'Generated with' or 'Co-Authored-By' lines, NO 'as an AI' phrases. Plain professional prose.\n\nSave the body to /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md and reply with STANCE: built | failed"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-polish-45a9",
      "name": "polish",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Polisher",
          "prompt_template": "Read /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md. Tighten it: remove redundant phrases, make it concise. Preserve all technical content. NO emoji, NO AI tells.\n\nOverwrite the file with the polished version. STANCE: rewrote | failed"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-scrub-8bc9",
      "name": "scrub",
      "type": "lmctl/shell-step",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "command": "perl /home/mma/bugfix/factory/pr_lint.pl /tmp/lmctl-next-pr-draft.md",
        "outcomes_from_exit": {
          "0": "@terminal:exit_0",
          "default": "@terminal:exit_default"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-finalize-116e",
      "name": "finalize",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "writes_to_project_path": true,
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "Move the polished PR body from /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md to {{project.local_path}}/PR_BODY.md so the operator can use it directly.\n\n1. cat /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md\n2. cp /tmp/lmctl-next-run-{{run_id}}-pr-draft.md {{project.local_path}}/PR_BODY.md\n3. Print the file path + size to confirm.\n\nSTANCE: finalized | failed"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-human-escalate-gate-4150",
      "name": "human_escalate_gate",
      "type": "lmctl/interactive",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "termination": {
          "operator_signal": true,
          "max_turns": 1
        }
      },
      "members": {
        "agent": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "initial_prompt_template": "Workflow ready for human submit. Branch + PR_BODY.md + diff are local; review and run: gh pr create --draft --base main --body-file PR_BODY.md\n\nWhen you have reviewed and chosen to approve or reject, signal done."
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-human-escalate-decide-53e6",
      "name": "human_escalate_decide",
      "type": "lmctl/review",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "max_loops": 5
      },
      "members": {
        "coder": {
          "team": "default",
          "alias": "Coder",
          "prompt_template": "The operator has reviewed the PR artifacts. Based on the conversation context, determine their decision.\n\nIf the operator approved: STANCE: approved\nIf the operator rejected: STANCE: rejected"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-aborted-ee8b",
      "name": "terminal:aborted",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "aborted",
        "kind": "failure"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-clarification-pr-a2ef",
      "name": "terminal:clarification_pr",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "clarification_pr",
        "kind": "neutral"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-not-reproducible-53e1",
      "name": "terminal:not_reproducible",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "not_reproducible",
        "kind": "neutral"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "s-terminal-pr-ready-ba07",
      "name": "terminal:pr_ready",
      "type": "lmctl/terminal",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "parameters": {
        "name": "pr_ready",
        "kind": "success"
      }
    }
  ],
